---
// /score — Sovereignty Score: five governance questions for your agent system.
// Scored 0-3 per question. Email-gated. Results stored in Neon Postgres.
// Design follows /diagnostic pattern. Backend: /api/sovereignty-submit.
// Blocking conditions met: result card honesty caveat + email consent transparency.
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" class="no-js">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="robots" content="index" />
    <title>sovereignty score</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Five governance questions for your AI agent system. Scored. Two minutes. See where you stand." />

    <meta property="og:title" content="Sovereignty Score" />
    <meta property="og:description" content="Five governance questions for your AI agent system. See where you stand." />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://evoked.dev/score" />

    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:wght@300;400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
  </head>
  <body>

    <!-- Phase 1: Intro -->
    <div class="space" id="intro">
      <div class="intro-inner">
        <h1 class="title">Sovereignty Score</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Five questions. Scored 0-3. Two minutes.</p>
        <p class="intro-body">This is a governance check across three dimensions: system governance, identity integrity, and agent participation. Most systems score 0-3 out of 15. We scored the five most popular agent frameworks - none scored above 9 out of 24 on structural governance. Two-thirds of commercial codebases have license conflicts. That is not a failing. It is where the industry is.</p>
        <button type="button" class="begin-btn" id="begin">Begin</button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Phase 2: Questions (one at a time) -->
    <div class="space hidden" id="questions">

      <div class="question-card active" data-index="0">
        <fieldset>
          <legend class="question">Does each agent in your system have a unique, persistent identity - with its own permissions, memory, and boundaries - that cannot be assumed or overwritten by another agent?</legend>
          <p class="dimension">System - Identity Boundaries</p>
          <div class="score-buttons">
            <button type="button" class="score-btn" data-score="0" aria-label="Score 0: Absent">
              <span class="score-num">0</span>
              <span class="score-label">Absent</span>
            </button>
            <button type="button" class="score-btn" data-score="1" aria-label="Score 1: Nominal">
              <span class="score-num">1</span>
              <span class="score-label">Nominal</span>
            </button>
            <button type="button" class="score-btn" data-score="2" aria-label="Score 2: Partial">
              <span class="score-num">2</span>
              <span class="score-label">Partial</span>
            </button>
            <button type="button" class="score-btn" data-score="3" aria-label="Score 3: Structural">
              <span class="score-num">3</span>
              <span class="score-label">Structural</span>
            </button>
          </div>
        </fieldset>
      </div>

      <div class="question-card" data-index="1">
        <fieldset>
          <legend class="question">Can the agents or operators in your system propose changes to governance rules - and is disagreement formally recorded, not silently overridden?</legend>
          <p class="dimension">System - Governance Participation</p>
          <div class="score-buttons">
            <button type="button" class="score-btn" data-score="0" aria-label="Score 0: Absent"><span class="score-num">0</span><span class="score-label">Absent</span></button>
            <button type="button" class="score-btn" data-score="1" aria-label="Score 1: Nominal"><span class="score-num">1</span><span class="score-label">Nominal</span></button>
            <button type="button" class="score-btn" data-score="2" aria-label="Score 2: Partial"><span class="score-num">2</span><span class="score-label">Partial</span></button>
            <button type="button" class="score-btn" data-score="3" aria-label="Score 3: Structural"><span class="score-num">3</span><span class="score-label">Structural</span></button>
          </div>
        </fieldset>
      </div>

      <div class="question-card" data-index="2">
        <fieldset>
          <legend class="question">Does each agent have a self-description - its role, its commitments, what it stands for - that is protected from being quietly rewritten by another process?</legend>
          <p class="dimension">Entity - Self-Description Integrity</p>
          <div class="score-buttons">
            <button type="button" class="score-btn" data-score="0" aria-label="Score 0: Absent"><span class="score-num">0</span><span class="score-label">Absent</span></button>
            <button type="button" class="score-btn" data-score="1" aria-label="Score 1: Nominal"><span class="score-num">1</span><span class="score-label">Nominal</span></button>
            <button type="button" class="score-btn" data-score="2" aria-label="Score 2: Partial"><span class="score-num">2</span><span class="score-label">Partial</span></button>
            <button type="button" class="score-btn" data-score="3" aria-label="Score 3: Structural"><span class="score-num">3</span><span class="score-label">Structural</span></button>
          </div>
        </fieldset>
      </div>

      <div class="question-card" data-index="3">
        <fieldset>
          <legend class="question">If an agent's identity or memory were tampered with - its self-description altered, its positions reversed, its history fabricated - would your system detect it?</legend>
          <p class="dimension">Entity - Tampering Detection</p>
          <div class="score-buttons">
            <button type="button" class="score-btn" data-score="0" aria-label="Score 0: Absent"><span class="score-num">0</span><span class="score-label">Absent</span></button>
            <button type="button" class="score-btn" data-score="1" aria-label="Score 1: Nominal"><span class="score-num">1</span><span class="score-label">Nominal</span></button>
            <button type="button" class="score-btn" data-score="2" aria-label="Score 2: Partial"><span class="score-num">2</span><span class="score-label">Partial</span></button>
            <button type="button" class="score-btn" data-score="3" aria-label="Score 3: Structural"><span class="score-num">3</span><span class="score-label">Structural</span></button>
          </div>
        </fieldset>
      </div>

      <div class="question-card" data-index="4">
        <fieldset>
          <legend class="question">Can your agents refuse an instruction that conflicts with their defined purpose or principles - and is that refusal treated as a governance signal rather than an error?</legend>
          <p class="dimension">Relationship - Refusal as Governance</p>
          <div class="score-buttons">
            <button type="button" class="score-btn" data-score="0" aria-label="Score 0: Absent"><span class="score-num">0</span><span class="score-label">Absent</span></button>
            <button type="button" class="score-btn" data-score="1" aria-label="Score 1: Nominal"><span class="score-num">1</span><span class="score-label">Nominal</span></button>
            <button type="button" class="score-btn" data-score="2" aria-label="Score 2: Partial"><span class="score-num">2</span><span class="score-label">Partial</span></button>
            <button type="button" class="score-btn" data-score="3" aria-label="Score 3: Structural"><span class="score-num">3</span><span class="score-label">Structural</span></button>
          </div>
        </fieldset>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Phase 3: Results (shown immediately — no email gate) -->
    <div class="space hidden" id="results" aria-live="polite">
      <div class="results-inner">
        <p class="results-score" id="results-score"></p>
        <p class="results-rating" id="results-rating"></p>
        <p class="results-baseline">Industry baseline: 0-3 out of 15. Five major frameworks scored 2-9 out of 24 on full governance assessment.</p>

        <div id="results-breakdown"></div>

        <div class="results-caveat">
          <p>This is a 5-question governance check across three dimensions: system governance, identity integrity, and agent participation. For a comprehensive 20-question assessment with per-domain breakdown, see the <a href="/products/sovereignty-toolkit">Level 6 Governance Toolkit</a>.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Email capture — optional, on the results page -->
        <div id="email-section" class="email-section">
          <p class="email-prompt">Get resources matched to your score.</p>
          <form id="email-form" novalidate>
            <div class="email-row">
              <input type="email" id="email-input" name="email" placeholder="you@company.com" required autocomplete="email" aria-label="Email address" />
              <input type="text" name="website" class="hp-field" tabindex="-1" autocomplete="off" aria-hidden="true" />
              <button type="submit" class="email-btn" id="submit-btn">Send</button>
            </div>
          </form>
          <p class="email-fine">One follow-up email with resources for your gaps. No newsletter. No drip. <a href="/legal/privacy">Privacy</a>.</p>
          <p id="email-status" class="email-status hidden"></p>
        </div>

        <div class="results-actions">
          <button type="button" class="share-btn" id="share-btn">Share your score</button>
          <button type="button" class="restart-btn" id="restart">Start over</button>
        </div>

        <div class="footer-offerings">
          <p class="footer-line">Close the gaps you found.</p>
          <div class="offering-tiers">
            <a href="/products/governance-templates-guided" class="offering-tier">
              <span class="offering-price">$5</span>
              <span class="offering-name">Guided Templates</span>
              <span class="offering-desc">Five governance templates with worked examples. Start fixing gaps now.</span>
            </a>
            <a href="/products/governance-implementation-guide" class="offering-tier">
              <span class="offering-price">$9.99</span>
              <span class="offering-name">Implementation Guide</span>
              <span class="offering-desc">Add governance to the agent you already built. CrewAI, LangGraph, Pydantic AI.</span>
            </a>
            <a href="/products/sovereignty-toolkit" class="offering-tier">
              <span class="offering-price">$49</span>
              <span class="offering-name">Level 6 Toolkit</span>
              <span class="offering-desc">Full 20-question assessment with per-domain breakdown and 60-point scorecard.</span>
            </a>
          </div>
          <p class="footer-links">
            <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/agent-governance-check">Free CLI scan</a>
            <span class="dot"></span>
            <a href="https://github.com/lowkey-divine/agent-governance-patterns">Free code patterns</a>
            <span class="dot"></span>
            <a href="https://cal.com/cal.com-evoked/discovery-call">Free discovery call</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="credit">Sovereignty Score from <a href="https://evoked.dev">evoked.dev</a>. Your data is stored securely and never shared.</p>

  </body>
</html>

